1619. Mean of Array After Removing Some Elements

1. arr.splice()
  1.if parameters are all positive: the 1st parameter is the index to start truncating, the 2nd parameter is the length to be truncated;
  2.if parameters include negative: the 1st parameter is the index to start truncating(from right to left), the 2nd parameter is the length to be truncated,
  and if the 2nd parameter is omitted, delete all the elements behind the 1st parameter;
2. type of data
  1.number type is the only way to represent a number in typescript;
  2.because the return value doesn't need to be rounded, so we use ordinary division operation(/) directly;
3. arr.reduce()
  1.reduce = for Loop = for...each Loop;
  2.it calls back every element that exists in the array;
  
method 1:
function trimMean(arr: number[]): number{
    arr.sort((a, b) => a - b);
    let len: number = arr.length * 0.05;
    arr.splice(0, len);
    arr.splice(-len);
    let sum: number = 0;
    for(let i: number = 0; i < arr.length; ++i){
        sum += arr[i];
    }
    return sum / arr.length;
};

method 2:
function trimMean(arr: number[]): number{
    arr.sort((a, b) => a - b);
    let len: number = arr.length * 0.05;
    arr.splice(0, len);
    arr.splice(-len);
    let sum: number = arr.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0);
    return sum / arr.length;
};
